{"ID":270358, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"358\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs357.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs359.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 358<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Forgiveness of Sins<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">All sins shall be forgiven, except the sin against the Holy Ghost;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> for Jesus will save all except\n  the sons of perdition.<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> What must a man do to commit the unpardonable sin?<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> He must receive the\n  Holy Ghost, have the heavens opened unto him,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> and know God,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and then sin against Him. After\n  a man has sinned against the Holy Ghost, there is no repentance for him.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span><span class=\"textFootRef\">,a<\/span> He has got to say that the\n  sun does not shine while he sees it; he has got to deny Jesus Christ<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> when the heavens have been\n  opened unto him,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and to deny the plan of salvation<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> with his eyes open to the truth of it; and from\n  that time he begins to be an enemy. This is the case with many apostates of the Church of Jesus\n  Christ of Latter-day Saints.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">When a man begins to be an enemy to this work, he hunts me, he seeks to kill me, and never\n  ceases to thirst for my blood.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> He gets the spirit of the devil<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span>&mdash;the same spirit that they had who\n  crucified the Lord of Life&mdash;the same spirit that sins against the Holy Ghost.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> You cannot save such\n  persons;<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> you cannot bring them to repentance; they make open war, like the devil,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and awful is\n  the consequence.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I advise all of you to be careful what you do, or you may by-and-by find out that you have been\n  deceived.<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> Stay yourselves;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> do not give way;<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> don&rsquo;t make any hasty moves, you may be saved.\n  If a spirit of bitterness<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> is in you, don&rsquo;t be in haste.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> You may say, that man is a sinner.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> Well, if\n  he repents, he shall be forgiven.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> Be cautious:<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> await. When you find a spirit that wants\n  bloodshed<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span>&mdash;murder, the same is not of God,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> but is of the devil.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> Out of the abundance of the\n  heart of man the mouth speaketh.<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">&ldquo;In My Father&rsquo;s House&rdquo;<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The best men bring forth the best works.<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> The man who tells you words of life<span class=\"footRef\">30<\/span> is the man who\n  can save you. I warn you against all evil characters who sin against the Holy Ghost;<span class=\"footRef\">31<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107970\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107970)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107970)\">Matt. 12:31-32<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116400\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116400)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116400)\">D&amp;C 132:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114430\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114430)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114430)\">D&amp;C 76:43<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111440\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111440)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111440)\">Jacob 7:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112252\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112252)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112252)\">Alma 39:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107444\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107444)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107444)\">Ezek. 1:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107796\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107796)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107796)\">Matt. 3:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108635\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108635)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108635)\">John 1:51<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109029\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109029)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109029)\">Acts 7:56<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110899\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110899)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110899)\">1 Ne. 1:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110965\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110965)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110965)\">1 Ne. 11:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112717\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112717)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112717)\">3 Ne. 28:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id