void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112876)\">Ether 8:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116790\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116790)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116790)\">Moses 5:29-31<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">28. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107980\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107980)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107980)\">Matt. 12:34<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">29. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107888\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107888)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107888)\">Matt. 7:20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">30. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108705\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108705)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108705)\">John 6:68<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114698\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114698)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114698)\">D&amp;C 84:43<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116845\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116845)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116845)\">Moses 6:59<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">31. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107971\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107971)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107971)\">Matt. 12:31-32<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n  <div class=\"textFootnotes\">\n    \n      <p class=\"std\"><span class=\"textMark\">a<\/span>&ldquo;For it is impossible for those who were once enlightened, and have tasted of the heavenly gift, and were made partakers of the Holy Ghost, and have tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the world to come, if they shall fall away, to renew them again unto repentance;\n        seeing they crucify to themselves the Son of God afresh, and put him to an open shame&rdquo; (Heb. 6:4-6). Those who sin against the light and knowledge of the Holy Ghost may be said to crucify more than the body of our Lord, they crucify the Spirit.<\/p>\n    \n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}